{"title":"Radical retro rides! Mongoose re-releases the Supergoose & California Special BMX bikes","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/22/radical-retro-rides-mongoose-re-releases-the-supergoose-california-special-bmx-bikes/","date":1632321613000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231207/Mongoose-Classic-Collection-title-shot-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Mongoose Classic Collection, whip\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231207/Mongoose-Classic-Collection-title-shot-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231207/Mongoose-Classic-Collection-title-shot-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231207/Mongoose-Classic-Collection-title-shot-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231207/Mongoose-Classic-Collection-title-shot-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231207/Mongoose-Classic-Collection-title-shot.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-272200\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>If you’re in your forties now, you probably remember neighbourhood kids (or perhaps yourself) cruising the streets on Mongoose’s early BMX bikes. Their Supergoose and California Special were iconic BMXs that introduced countless youth to the fun and freedom a bicycle can afford throughout the 1980’s.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231216/Mongoose-Supergoose-California-Special-replicas.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231216/Mongoose-Supergoose-California-Special-replicas.jpg\" alt=\"Mongoose Supergoose and California Special replicas\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231216/Mongoose-Supergoose-California-Special-replicas.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231216/Mongoose-Supergoose-California-Special-replicas-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231216/Mongoose-Supergoose-California-Special-replicas-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231216/Mongoose-Supergoose-California-Special-replicas-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a></p><p>Since achieving ‘retro’ status, the original Supergoose and California Special have both become collector’s items. Given the interest in these nostalgic bikes Mongoose is releasing a limited run of both models, which also serve to introduce the brand’s Classics Collection.</p><p>Mongoose says the reissued Supergoose and California Special are fully faithful remakes, featuring the same materials, geometry, specs and color schemes as the original bikes.</p><h3>California Special</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231201/Mongoose-California-Special-blue.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231201/Mongoose-California-Special-blue.jpg\" alt=\"Mongoose California Special, blue\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231201/Mongoose-California-Special-blue.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231201/Mongoose-California-Special-blue-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231201/Mongoose-California-Special-blue-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231201/Mongoose-California-Special-blue-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a></p><p>The replica California Special is based upon Mongoose’s original 1983 model year, and is built entirely from high tensile steel. If the chrome finish wasn’t enough, the head tube reinforcement and rear stay yokes simply scream 80’s style!</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231158/Mongoose-California-Special-Black.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231158/Mongoose-California-Special-Black.jpg\" alt=\"Mongoose California Special, black\" width=\"717\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231158/Mongoose-California-Special-Black.jpg 717w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231158/Mongoose-California-Special-Black-269x300.jpg 269w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231158/Mongoose-California-Special-Black-108x120.jpg 108w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 717px) 100vw, 717px\"></a></p><p>This steel steed rides on Mongoose’s drilled alloy Pro Class rims wrapped with gumwall Snake Belly tires. &nbsp;Braking is handled (somewhat..!) by period-accurate Dia Compe MX brakes and levers, and the handlebar looks surprisingly modern for 1983.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231203/Mongoose-California-Special-Red.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231203/Mongoose-California-Special-Red.jpg\" alt=\"Mongoose California Special, red\" width=\"800\" height=\"543\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231203/Mongoose-California-Special-Red.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231203/Mongoose-California-Special-Red-297x202.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231203/Mongoose-California-Special-Red-120x81.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231203/Mongoose-California-Special-Red-768x521.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a></p><p>The chrome California Special gets three different color schemes: Blue, red or black. Each boasts a selection of color-matched parts including a set of Mongoose Pro Series pads, tires, grips, seats, brake calipers and levers, and even the cable housing.</p><h3>Supergoose</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231219/Mongoose-Supergoose-Red.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231219/Mongoose-Supergoose-Red.jpg\" alt=\"Mongoose Supergoose, red\" width=\"800\" height=\"540\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231219/Mongoose-Supergoose-Red.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231219/Mongoose-Supergoose-Red-297x200.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231219/Mongoose-Supergoose-Red-120x81.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231219/Mongoose-Supergoose-Red-768x518.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a></p><p>While it first launched in 1979, the replica Supergoose is based upon the ‘looptail’ frame design introduced in 1984. The Supergoose features a full 4130 chromoly frame, and rolls on Mongoose’s Pro Class rims. It also features Mongoose Pro Class handlebars, Dia Compe MX brakes and levers, a hinged Dia Compe seat clamp, and of course a retro three-piece pad set.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231213/Mongoose-Supergoose-black-close-up.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231213/Mongoose-Supergoose-black-close-up.jpg\" alt=\"Mongoose Supergoose, black, close up\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231213/Mongoose-Supergoose-black-close-up.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231213/Mongoose-Supergoose-black-close-up-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231213/Mongoose-Supergoose-black-close-up-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231213/Mongoose-Supergoose-black-close-up-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a></p><p>To match the old school originals the Supergoose gets two colorways – A red frame with blue components, or a black frame with red accents. The pad set, tires, seats, grips, chainrings and even cable housings are all color-coded to ensure an authentic look.</p><div id=\"attachment_272205\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231210/Mongoose-retro-packaging.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-272205\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231210/Mongoose-retro-packaging.jpg\" alt=\"Mongoose retro bike box\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231210/Mongoose-retro-packaging.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231210/Mongoose-retro-packaging-297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231210/Mongoose-retro-packaging-120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20231210/Mongoose-retro-packaging-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-272205\">Images c. Mongoose</p></div><p>For added collector appeal, these bikes will ship out in ‘80’s inspired white litho-laminated boxes that feature classic Mongoose artwork. The Supergoose sells for $549.99 and the California Special costs $449.99. Both models are expected to ship in late October.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.mongoose.com/\"><em>mongoose.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Steve Fisher","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"b6b21f32405bae3197860a1be1f5a892cc93fc2ae0e2610305c4aae55fc62d87","category":"Cycling"}